30,000 ₫</b>, optional.</li><li><b>Insurance</b> (basic third-party) — a token <b>~60,000–100,000 ₫ a year</b>, technically required.</li></ul><h2>Monthly total</h2><p>With normal riding around Nha Trang, running a 50cc costs about <b>300,000–600,000 ₫ a month</b> (≈ $12–24). That&rsquo;s cheaper than a few taxi/Grab trips in a week. A bike really saves money.</p><h2>Bottom line</h2><p>Running a 50cc in Nha Trang is pennies. So for two weeks or more, <a href="arenda-vs-pokupka-en.html">buying (especially with a 50% buy-back)</a> almost always beats renting and taxis. Our bikes come <b>serviced before sale</b> with clean papers — fewer surprise costs. To make the bike last, see <a href="uhod-za-baikom-en.html">scooter care</a>.</p><p style="margin-top:24px"><a href="catalog-en.html" class="btn btn-wa">See bikes &rarr;</a> <a href="arenda-vs-pokupka-en.html" class="btn btn-tg" style="margin-left:8px">Rent or buy &rarr;</a></p></div></section><footer><div class="wrap"><div class="fgrid"><div><h4>50cc bikes in Nha Trang</h4><p>Honest 50cc bikes (scooters). Police-checked, gentle mileage, serviced, warranty and 50% buy-back.</p><div class="pay"><span>₫ VND</span><span>$ USD</span><span>USDT</span><span>Cash</span></div></div><div><h4>Menu</h4><a href="catalog-en.html">Catalog</a><a href="vykup-en.html">How it works</a><a href="kak-kupit-en.html">How to buy</a><a href="blog-en.html">Articles</a><a href="o-nas-en.html">About</a></div><div><h4>Contacts</h4><a href="https://wa.me/84386818874">WhatsApp</a><a href="https://t.me/babaskin_o">Telegram</a><a href="https://instagram.com/bike50cc_nha_trang">Instagram</a><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/jsxikqy9AZMNtmAE6" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Maps</a><p>Nha Trang · daily</p></div></div><div class="copy">© 2026 50cc bikes in Nha Trang. All rights reserved.</div></div></footer></body></html>